channel.title: Compiling errors
channel.description:
i was compiling, and i entered the invincible command, and it still wont work! for some reason, the variable IsDead is not being recognized. is there a different ..Dead variable for Richscape? this is the compiler errors:
[code]:: Preparing for compile... :: Auto-setting envriomental variables... :: :: Scanning for latest JDK version... :: :: Found JDK 1.6.0_03 :: Results: client.java:13367: cannot find symbol symbol : variable IsDead location: class client if(IsDead); ^ client.java:13368: cannot find symbol symbol : variable IsDead location: class client IsDead = false; ^ client.java:13373: cannot find symbol symbol : variable IsDead location: class client if(IsDead); ^ client.java:13374: cannot find symbol symbol : variable IsDead location: class client IsDead = true; ^ Note: Some input files use or override a deprecated API. Note: Recompile with -Xlint:deprecation for details. 4 errors :: Done! Press any key to continue . . .[/code]
how can i fix this. ive tried a couple of debugs, but they wont work...
